
Burhanuddin () is an Upazila (or sub-district) of Bhola District in the Division of Barisal, Bangladesh.

Geography
Burhanuddin is located at . It has 37413 units of house hold and total area 284.67 km².

Demographics
As of 1991 Bangladesh census, Burhanuddin has a population of 208478. Males constitute are 51.13% of the population, and females 48.87%. This Upazila's eighteen up population is 94581. Burhanuddin has an average literacy rate of 21.2% (7+ years), and the national average of 32.4% literate. ;;

Administrative
Burhanuddin has 9 Unions/Wards, 57 Mauzas/Mahallas, and 52 villages. 


